questions.question:
Consider the following languages.
L1 = {<M> | M takes at least 2016 steps on some input}
L2 = {<M> | M takes at least 2016 steps on all inputs}
L3 = {<M> | M accepts epsilon}
where for each Turing machine M, <M> denotes a specific encoding of M.

Which one of the following is TRUE?

A. L1 is recursive and L2, L3 are not recursive
B. L2 is recursive and L1, L3 are not recursive
C. L1, L2 are recursive and L3 is not recursive
D. L1, L2, L3 are all recursive

Let <M> denote an encoding of an automaton M. Suppose that Sigma = {0, 1}. Which of the following languages is/are NOT recursive?

A. L = {<M> | M is a DFA such that L(M) = {0}^*}
B. L = {<M> | M is a DFA such that L(M) = {0}}
C. L = {<M> | M is a PDA such that L(M) = {0}^*}
D. L = {<M> | M is a PDA such that L(M) = {0}^*}
